00:00:22.590 --> 00:00:23.890
&gt;&gt; Good afternoon.

00:00:23.890 --> 00:00:27.940
Good afternoon everyone and
thank you all for coming here.

00:00:27.940 --> 00:00:31.450
I'm Mary-Jane Deeb, Chief of the
African and Middle East Division

00:00:31.450 --> 00:00:36.750
and I would like to welcome you
to this very special program.

00:00:36.750 --> 00:00:42.580
I always begin with a few
statements about our division

00:00:42.580 --> 00:00:46.360
and our division is made
up of three sections.

00:00:46.360 --> 00:00:51.900 position:56%
The African section, the [inaudible]
section and the Neri section.

00:00:51.900 --> 00:00:58.420
And between the three
section we cover 78 countries.

00:00:58.420 --> 00:01:05.110
Most - well all of Africa, North
African, sub-Saharan Africa,

00:01:05.110 --> 00:01:12.510 position:56%
the whole Middle East and that
expands to Afghanistan, central Asia

00:01:12.510 --> 00:01:18.380
and the Caucasus and the
Hebraic world worldwide.

00:01:18.380 --> 00:01:26.850
So we collect from and
about this large region.

00:01:26.850 --> 00:01:40.630
We collect via our offices in
Cairo, in Nairobi, in Islamabad,

00:01:40.630 --> 00:01:45.300
and the materials come
directly from those officers.

00:01:45.300 --> 00:01:51.960
They catalog there, they come to
us and then we put them in our -

00:01:51.960 --> 00:01:57.990
on our decks and we serve them to
patrons here in our reading room.

00:01:57.990 --> 00:02:00.630
But we don't only do that.

00:02:00.630 --> 00:02:04.300
We don't only serve those books,
we don't only acquire them.

00:02:04.300 --> 00:02:07.670
We always do programs around
them and we do programs

00:02:07.670 --> 00:02:11.720
about the region, about
our 78 countries.

00:02:11.720 --> 00:02:19.380
We feel that these materials
are alive and need to connect

00:02:19.380 --> 00:02:24.310
with people and we do so directly.

00:02:24.310 --> 00:02:29.980
